Breakfast/Pasteries -
	Thierry - very good iced hot mocha, fancy pasteries
	Medina Cafe - REALLY good breakfast/lunch place with waffles
  
Lunch - 
  Nosherie - to go salad place  in Telus garden
	Finch’s  light lunch but sandwiches that come wrapped really cutely
  Nosh - fun sandwiches lower on the list though
  
Dinner -
	Cactus Club Cafe - right by the convention center so maybe make reservations
	Espana Restaurant - very good tapas
	Chewies - southern food with really good beneights
  Nando’s - fast order at a counter chicken place w/ nice sides
  
Also a fun fact about me is that I really like grocery stores - Urban Fair is my favorite in Vancouver.

Weekend Places to visit (might need to double check what it is like in winter)
	Bike around Standley park + see aquarium
	See a hockey game with the canucks
	Lynn Canyon Bridge
	Hike Stawamus Chief
	Granville island market
	Kitslano Beach (very cute neighborhood with one cute downntown) + Wreck beach by UBC (lots of logs on a beach) 
